<h3>Generator Options</h3>

<ul>
  <li><code>--stimulus</code>: Generates a new Stimulus controller named <code>badge_controller.js</code> and registers it for enhanced interactivity</li>
  <li><code>--directory</code>: Customize the component location (defaults to <code>app/views/rui/components</code>)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Component Properties</h3>
<ul>
  <li><code>label</code>: Fallback text if no block content is passed</li>
  <li><code>color</code>: Color theme variants:
    <ul>
      <li><code>:primary</code>, <code>:secondary</code>, <code>:gray</code>, <code>:red</code>, <code>:orange</code>, <code>:yellow</code>, <code>:green</code>, <code>:blue</code>, <code>:indigo</code>, <code>:purple</code>, <code>:pink</code>, <code>:white</code></li>
      <li>Default: <code>:gray</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><code>variant</code>: Style variants:
    <ul>
      <li><code>:solid</code> (filled background), <code>:pill</code> (rounded full), <code>:outline</code> (border style), <code>:tag</code> (dismissible tag with X button)</li>
      <li>Default: <code>:solid</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><code>dismissible</code>: Adds dismiss button to tag variant only:
    <ul>
      <li>Defaults to <code>true</code> for <code>:tag</code> variant.</li>
      <li>Set to <code>false</code> to disable dismiss button on tags. The X icon will still display.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><code>classes</code>: Additional CSS classes for badge styling</li>
  <li><code>content</code>: Passed automatically from <code>rui</code> block or fallback to label</li>
</ul>

<h3>Notes</h3>
<ul>
  <li>The <code>:tag</code> variant is dismissible by default and requires <code>badge_controller.js</code> for functionality. Run <code>rails g railsui:component Badge --stimulus</code> to generate the accompanying Stimulus controller with some boilerplate code.</li>
  <li>Dismiss functionality uses client-side JavaScript to fade out and remove the badge. You'll need to persist this to the database.</li>
</ul>

